column5: Is there any way to get from International Falls airport to Dryden without renting a car and approximate cost?
You could hitch hike if you're really cheap😂One bus route goes to Thunder Bay and then Dryden, quite a long ride if I remember correctly.
You can call Rusty Myers and get a quote... but it is going to be very expensive.
Did you check with your Lodge or Outfitter?
You can try City Cab in International Falls. They run van services to many cities in Canada every day. 218-283-8635
When? Many on here going that way every week. I will be going through there on the morning of Aug 24th. Could give you a ride then. You buy breakfast...
Sunset Transportation out of Kenora has private shuttles to wherever you want to go. 807-548-1450 -FT
